{"word":"φρουρός","slug":"φρουρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φρουρός</b></el> <el>(φρουρός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><p/><i>a watcher, guard</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:contracted, contraction'>Contr.</a> for <el>προουρός</el>, as <a href='S:φροῦδος'><el>φροῦδος</el></a> from <el>πρὸ ὁδοῦ.</el>\n"}]}